Key statistics:
https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22757596/
27% of truckers suffer from loneliness

https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20701418/
 "truckers face many occupational stressors including constant time pressures, social isolation, disrespectful treatment from others, 
driving hazards such as weather changes, traffic, and road conditions, and violence or fear of violence"

"Trucking has been classified as one of the highest-risk occupations in the United States. Occupational stress is even greater for 
long-haul truckers who are away from home, family, friends, and other support networks for several days or weeks at a time."
